citations:
    citation-agot-jon-x:
        source: source-agot
        properties:
            locator: "Jon X"
            text_from_source: "The pommel was a hunk of pale stone weighted with lead to balance the long blade. It had been carved into the likeness of a snarling wolf's head, with chips of garnet set into the eyes … 'It did, once. Longclaw, it was called.'"
            accessed: "2026-03-06"
        notes: "Jon Snow recovering from burned right hand (sustained fighting the wight Othor). Lord Commander Mormont gives Jon the Valyrian steel bastard sword Longclaw — the ancestral Mormont blade, bear-head pommel recarved as a wolf's head. Halder (builder) carved the stone pommel; Sam bought the garnets in Mole's Town. Ser Alliser Thorne is sent to Eastwatch-by-the-Sea, then to King's Landing with the severed wight hand, to show Joffrey proof of the threat beyond the Wall. Ser Endrew Tarth named new master-at-arms, coming from Shadow Tower. Jon learns of Robb's march south from Sam. Maester Aemon reveals to Jon he is Aemon Targaryen, grandson of King Maekar I (Maekar I > Aemon + Aegon V), great-uncle to Aerys II. He chose the Night's Watch over the Iron Throne. He counsels Jon that choosing between duty and love is the burden every man faces. Ser Jaremy Rykker confirmed dead (killed by the wight Jafer Flowers)."
